##
Kind: captions

00:00:06.941 --> 00:00:09.476 position:7% line:83% align:start
[woman] What the hell is wrong
with these eggs?

00:00:10.712 --> 00:00:11.880 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Father Pucchi] My Stand...

00:00:11.913 --> 00:00:14.147 position:13% line:83% align:start
I haven't the vaguest idea
what it is,

00:00:14.181 --> 00:00:16.149 position:16% line:83% align:start
but it's painfully clear
that it's no longer Pale Snake.

00:00:18.018 --> 00:00:20.287 position:10% line:89% align:start
What is it? What could it be?

00:00:21.823 --> 00:00:23.725 position:24% line:89% align:start
I feel terrible...

00:00:23.758 --> 00:00:27.394 position:13% line:83% align:start
Something is quickly raging
out of control inside of me.

00:00:27.427 --> 00:00:29.062 position:21% line:83% align:start
There's some kind of
independent power

00:00:29.096 --> 00:00:30.732 position:16% line:89% align:start
that's ignoring my will.

00:00:31.833 --> 00:00:34.736 position:35% line:83% align:start
But oddly,
I feel hope in this power.

00:00:34.769 --> 00:00:38.105 position:16% line:83% align:start
Hope, in fact, is the one
and only thing I feel from it.

00:00:38.138 --> 00:00:41.609 position:24% line:83% align:start
Dio's note recorded
in Jotaro's memories...

00:00:41.643 --> 00:00:44.746 position:13% line:83% align:start
Perhaps that is what I need
to control this power, then.

00:00:45.580 --> 00:00:47.214 position:21% line:89% align:start
The time and place...

00:00:47.247 --> 00:00:49.918 position:30% line:83% align:start
North latitude,
28 degrees 24 minutes.

00:00:49.951 --> 00:00:52.620 position:30% line:83% align:start
West longitude,
80 degrees 36 minutes.

00:00:52.654 --> 00:00:56.189 position:13% line:83% align:start
Delightful. Heaven appears
to be there, after all,

00:00:56.223 --> 00:01:00.127 position:27% line:83% align:start
and that place is
at Cape Canaveral Space Center,

00:01:00.160 --> 00:01:01.361 position:30% line:89% align:start
to be precise.

00:01:02.162 --> 00:01:05.065 position:27% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music]

00:01:05.098 --> 00:01:07.869 position:7% line:83% align:start
At the beginning of everything,
there was gravity.

00:01:07.902 --> 00:01:10.437 position:10% line:89% align:start
Even this round Earth of ours

00:01:10.470 --> 00:01:13.273 position:16% line:83% align:start
was brought into reality
with gravity.

00:01:13.307 --> 00:01:14.374 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Anastasia] No way!

00:01:14.809 --> 00:01:16.544 position:38% line:89% align:start
[smashes]

00:01:16.578 --> 00:01:18.312 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Ermes]
We're gonna keep falling!

00:01:18.345 --> 00:01:22.349 position:19% line:83% align:start
We're not falling down,
we're falling backwards!

00:01:22.382 --> 00:01:25.053 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Jolyne] No, this can't be! Is
this the priest's new ability?

00:01:25.085 --> 00:01:25.587 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[belt clicks]
-[yelps]

00:01:25.620 --> 00:01:27.689 position:38% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:01:27.722 --> 00:01:29.891 position:13% line:83% align:start
Jolyne! Here, you grab hold
of Emporio!

00:01:29.924 --> 00:01:31.793 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[screams]
-[Jolyne grunts]

00:01:31.826 --> 00:01:33.293 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Anastasia] Diver Drive!

00:01:35.128 --> 00:01:36.463 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Ermes grunts]

00:01:36.496 --> 00:01:37.264 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:01:39.033 --> 00:01:40.835 position:41% line:89% align:start
Ermes!

00:01:42.737 --> 00:01:44.404 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Father Pucchi] And with
its gravitational pull,

00:01:44.438 --> 00:01:47.174 position:24% line:83% align:start
the Earth continues
to revolve around the Sun!

00:01:47.207 --> 00:01:48.810 position:27% line:83% align:start
The question that
still remains is,

00:01:48.843 --> 00:01:50.778 position:30% line:83% align:start
where on earth
am I headed now?

00:01:50.812 --> 00:01:52.479 position:10% line:89% align:start
What is going to happen next?

00:01:53.213 --> 00:01:54.716 position:10% line:89% align:start
I knew my old man sealed away

00:01:54.749 --> 00:01:56.884 position:21% line:83% align:start
some sort of ability
in Egypt 20 years ago,

00:01:56.918 --> 00:01:58.653 position:24% line:89% align:start
but this is insane!

00:01:58.686 --> 00:02:02.255 position:10% line:83% align:start
This must be the "heaven" the
priest has been searching for!

00:02:02.289 --> 00:02:05.827 position:16% line:83% align:start
Within my body and spirit
lies the existence of gravity,

00:02:05.860 --> 00:02:08.295 position:19% line:83% align:start
and it shall also exist
at the end of the world!

00:02:09.396 --> 00:02:11.766 position:30% line:83% align:start
There's our way
into the Visitor Center.

00:02:11.799 --> 00:02:15.069 position:7% line:83% align:start
Jolyne, are you sure the priest
is still in this direction?

00:02:15.103 --> 00:02:17.605 position:27% line:83% align:start
He's close, yeah.
I can sense him right here.

00:02:17.639 --> 00:02:21.643 position:27% line:89% align:start
[menacing music]

00:02:21.676 --> 00:02:24.277 position:13% line:83% align:start
It almost feels like he was
just standing in this spot.

00:02:29.684 --> 00:02:31.351 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Emporio]
This is the priest's Stand?

00:02:31.385 --> 00:02:32.654 position:21% line:89% align:start
Is it in a new form?

00:02:33.788 --> 00:02:36.791 position:33% line:89% align:start
[theme music]

00:04:04.411 --> 00:04:06.246 position:33% line:83% align:start
-[squelches]
-[Jolyne screams]

00:04:06.279 --> 00:04:08.216 position:19% line:89% align:start
What's up with my hand?

00:04:08.248 --> 00:04:11.351 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Stand] I've come
to eliminate you for good,

00:04:11.384 --> 00:04:13.221 position:19% line:83% align:start
since you couldn't wait
two more days.

00:04:13.253 --> 00:04:14.354 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:04:14.387 --> 00:04:17.759 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Stand] Jolyne Cujoh!

00:04:18.391 --> 00:04:19.227 position:33% line:83% align:start
-[splatters]
-[gasps]

00:04:19.259 --> 00:04:22.096 position:10% line:89% align:start
My arm's turning inside out!

00:04:22.130 --> 00:04:24.599 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Jolyne!
-Hey! Are you okay?

00:04:24.632 --> 00:04:26.433 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Stand hisses]

00:04:26.466 --> 00:04:29.637 position:13% line:83% align:start
Are you the friend who was
aiding Jolyne in prison?

00:04:29.670 --> 00:04:31.304 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:04:31.338 --> 00:04:34.474 position:10% line:83% align:start
Go, Emporio! Hurry up and run
to where Anastasia is!

00:04:35.143 --> 00:04:35.977 position:35% line:83% align:start
[grunting]
Stone Ocean!

00:04:36.544 --> 00:04:37.979 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:04:38.513 --> 00:04:38.946 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:04:38.980 --> 00:04:40.615 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Emporio yelps]

00:04:41.281 --> 00:04:43.251 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne grunts nervously]

00:04:43.283 --> 00:04:45.418 position:7% line:89% align:start
Jolyne, he circled behind you!

00:04:45.452 --> 00:04:46.754 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Stand whirrs, zaps]

00:04:46.788 --> 00:04:48.355 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Jolyne] Oraa, oraa, oraa,
oraa, oraa, oraa, oraa!

00:04:50.224 --> 00:04:50.925 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Stand grunts]

00:04:51.391 --> 00:04:51.993 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne grunts]

00:04:53.360 --> 00:04:54.361 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Anastasia gasps]

00:04:55.428 --> 00:04:57.098 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Stand]
First order of business,

00:04:57.131 --> 00:04:59.700 position:16% line:89% align:start
dispose of Jolyne Cujoh.

00:04:59.734 --> 00:05:01.969 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Jolyne] Anastasia,
hurry up and come over here!

00:05:02.003 --> 00:05:03.938 position:41% line:83% align:start
-[rips]
-[both gasp]

00:05:03.971 --> 00:05:05.873 position:27% line:89% align:start
[thrilling music]

00:05:06.774 --> 00:05:07.775 position:35% line:89% align:start
[cracking]

00:05:07.809 --> 00:05:10.178 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne gasps]

00:05:10.211 --> 00:05:12.580 position:27% line:89% align:start
[menacing music]

00:05:12.613 --> 00:05:14.582 position:13% line:89% align:start
What in the world is this?

00:05:14.615 --> 00:05:17.350 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's like your hair turned in
on itself, Jolyne.

00:05:17.384 --> 00:05:18.219 position:21% line:89% align:start
And so did my cleats.

00:05:18.252 --> 00:05:20.221 position:27% line:83% align:start
-[metal swishes]
-[both gasp]

00:05:20.254 --> 00:05:22.223 position:30% line:89% align:start
[metal clunks]

00:05:22.256 --> 00:05:24.659 position:10% line:83% align:start
It must be his attacks, like
from when his fist grazed us,

00:05:24.692 --> 00:05:27.528 position:13% line:89% align:start
but it barely made contact.

00:05:27.562 --> 00:05:30.397 position:21% line:83% align:start
So, if he punches us,
we'll be in big trouble.

00:05:31.132 --> 00:05:33.134 position:7% line:89% align:start
Gravity, judging by everything

00:05:33.167 --> 00:05:34.535 position:21% line:83% align:start
that's been happening
around us...

00:05:34.569 --> 00:05:37.538 position:19% line:83% align:start
This probably has to do
with gravity too, Jolyne.

00:05:37.572 --> 00:05:39.874 position:19% line:83% align:start
Whether it be an apple
or the planet itself,

00:05:39.907 --> 00:05:42.176 position:24% line:83% align:start
everything on Earth
is affected by gravity,

00:05:42.210 --> 00:05:43.744 position:7% line:89% align:start
and all of it is pulled towards

00:05:43.778 --> 00:05:45.613 position:35% line:83% align:start
the Earth's
gravitational center!

00:05:45.646 --> 00:05:47.748 position:19% line:83% align:start
That's the natural law
of the universe.

00:05:47.782 --> 00:05:50.551 position:13% line:83% align:start
Except, this guy's ability
messes with that.

00:05:50.585 --> 00:05:52.887 position:21% line:83% align:start
It makes the gravity
go in the opposite direction!

00:05:52.920 --> 00:05:53.955 position:24% line:83% align:start
That's why whenever
his Stand's fists

00:05:53.988 --> 00:05:55.857 position:10% line:89% align:start
make contact with something,

00:05:55.890 --> 00:05:57.457 position:24% line:89% align:start
it'll be inverted!

00:05:57.490 --> 00:06:00.294 position:16% line:83% align:start
And I don't know how far,
but with everything sideways,

00:06:00.328 --> 00:06:01.863 position:16% line:89% align:start
we're gonna keep falling.

00:06:01.896 --> 00:06:02.997 position:30% line:89% align:start
So this is it.

00:06:03.030 --> 00:06:05.867 position:13% line:83% align:start
Thanks to the unique energy
around Cape Canaveral,

00:06:05.900 --> 00:06:08.002 position:19% line:83% align:start
the priest has somehow
developed a new Stand.

00:06:09.070 --> 00:06:10.571 position:16% line:89% align:start
It's no longer Pale Snake

00:06:10.605 --> 00:06:12.907 position:21% line:83% align:start
which had the ability
to manipulate memories,

00:06:12.940 --> 00:06:15.810 position:7% line:83% align:start
nor does it have the ability to
split itself in half infinitely

00:06:15.843 --> 00:06:16.143 position:21% line:89% align:start
like the Green Baby.

00:06:18.913 --> 00:06:21.148 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Anastasia] Jolyne,
he's coming back around!

00:06:21.182 --> 00:06:23.117 position:24% line:83% align:start
I need you to jump
toward Anastasia.

00:06:23.150 --> 00:06:24.619 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Now, Emporio!
-[shrieks]

00:06:25.353 --> 00:06:26.187 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Anastasia grunts]

00:06:26.220 --> 00:06:27.387 position:30% line:89% align:start
[metal creaks]

00:06:27.420 --> 00:06:28.856 position:38% line:89% align:start
[smashes]

00:06:28.890 --> 00:06:29.590 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne grunts]

00:06:31.292 --> 00:06:32.226 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:06:32.260 --> 00:06:33.561 position:30% line:89% align:start
[rapid whirrs]

00:06:34.095 --> 00:06:35.263 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne] Oraa!

00:06:35.296 --> 00:06:37.031 position:33% line:83% align:start
-[Stand gags]
-[Anastasia exclaims]

00:06:37.064 --> 00:06:38.232 position:27% line:89% align:start
Wow, she did it!

00:06:38.266 --> 00:06:40.067 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[thumps]
-[all gasp]

00:06:41.401 --> 00:06:42.803 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Anastasia] Are you kidding me?

00:06:43.738 --> 00:06:47.275 position:35% line:89% align:start
[cracking]

00:06:47.308 --> 00:06:48.776 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne] It's inverting!

00:06:48.809 --> 00:06:49.810 position:41% line:89% align:start
Jolyne!

00:06:50.878 --> 00:06:51.779 position:41% line:89% align:start
[thuds]

00:06:53.114 --> 00:06:55.016 position:13% line:89% align:start
No way, that's impossible!

00:06:55.049 --> 00:06:57.450 position:24% line:89% align:start
[cracks, squelches]

00:06:57.484 --> 00:06:59.020 position:27% line:89% align:start
[whines in panic]

00:06:59.053 --> 00:06:59.120 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne] Don't panic, Emporio.

00:06:59.754 --> 00:07:01.488 position:35% line:89% align:start
[both] Huh?

00:07:01.522 --> 00:07:02.757 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Jolyne] You don't have
to get so upset.

00:07:02.790 --> 00:07:06.394 position:13% line:83% align:start
If I get turned inside out
every time he hits me,

00:07:06.426 --> 00:07:08.296 position:16% line:83% align:start
that just means I'll have
to let him hit me again

00:07:08.329 --> 00:07:10.898 position:16% line:83% align:start
so that I can flip myself
back to normal.

00:07:11.832 --> 00:07:13.401 position:24% line:83% align:start
So he can invert me
all he wants to...

00:07:13.433 --> 00:07:16.103 position:16% line:83% align:start
'cause I'll just hit him
with the reverse!

00:07:16.570 --> 00:07:18.471 position:30% line:89% align:start
[action music]

00:07:18.506 --> 00:07:20.741 position:27% line:89% align:start
[blood splatters]

00:07:20.775 --> 00:07:21.842 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[Stand hisses]
-[both gasp]

00:07:22.376 --> 00:07:23.778 position:33% line:89% align:start
You're okay!

00:07:23.811 --> 00:07:25.513 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Jolyne]
Oh, good freaking grief.

00:07:25.546 --> 00:07:26.514 position:30% line:89% align:start
Gimme a break.

00:07:26.981 --> 00:07:28.215 position:27% line:89% align:start
It does the job,

00:07:28.249 --> 00:07:31.686 position:13% line:83% align:start
but I still have to sew my
wounds back up with my thread.

00:07:31.719 --> 00:07:33.688 position:16% line:83% align:start
Although thanks to that,
there's one thing I'm sure of.

00:07:33.721 --> 00:07:37.658 position:7% line:83% align:start
Lucky for us, as long as we can
hit him, he'll take damage.

00:07:37.692 --> 00:07:40.661 position:7% line:83% align:start
But it's looking like I should
finish this guy off

00:07:40.695 --> 00:07:42.029 position:24% line:89% align:start
right here and now!

00:07:43.164 --> 00:07:44.632 position:21% line:89% align:start
[action choral music]

00:07:48.636 --> 00:07:50.538 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Anastasia]
Ugh, I can't be babysitting.

00:07:50.571 --> 00:07:52.440 position:10% line:89% align:start
Go, Emporio. Start climbing.

00:07:52.472 --> 00:07:54.675 position:33% line:83% align:start
Make your way
up to that handrail.

00:07:54.709 --> 00:07:56.277 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'm not here for you.

00:07:56.310 --> 00:07:57.477 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'm here to make sure

00:07:57.511 --> 00:07:59.880 position:27% line:83% align:start
my darling Jolyne
has backup if she needs it!

00:07:59.914 --> 00:08:00.548 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Emporio] Yeah!

00:08:00.581 --> 00:08:02.516 position:27% line:89% align:start
[hisses, snarls]

00:08:02.550 --> 00:08:04.418 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne grunts]

00:08:04.452 --> 00:08:05.519 position:30% line:89% align:start
[action music]

00:08:16.163 --> 00:08:17.131 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Stand hisses]

00:08:18.032 --> 00:08:20.134 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne strains]

00:08:20.167 --> 00:08:21.202 position:38% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:08:23.437 --> 00:08:24.605 position:30% line:89% align:start
[metal creaks]

00:08:24.905 --> 00:08:25.806 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:08:27.341 --> 00:08:28.509 position:35% line:89% align:start
Jolyne, no!

00:08:28.542 --> 00:08:31.045 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Stand] This ticket box
you're clinging onto

00:08:32.313 --> 00:08:33.881 position:19% line:83% align:start
has already been turned
inside out.

00:08:33.914 --> 00:08:36.484 position:27% line:89% align:start
[metal clanking]

00:08:36.517 --> 00:08:38.486 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[metal whomps]
-[gasps, strains]

00:08:38.986 --> 00:08:40.221 position:27% line:89% align:start
[menacing music]

00:08:42.923 --> 00:08:44.925 position:35% line:89% align:start
[clanking]

00:08:47.061 --> 00:08:50.064 position:30% line:83% align:start
[grunts, gasps]
What's up with his movements?

00:08:50.798 --> 00:08:52.166 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne] Judging by its power,

00:08:52.199 --> 00:08:54.602 position:27% line:83% align:start
I thought it'd be
an automated pursuit Stand,

00:08:54.635 --> 00:08:56.670 position:30% line:83% align:start
but his attacks
are way too precise!

00:08:57.506 --> 00:08:58.507 position:21% line:89% align:start
And he's not focused

00:08:58.539 --> 00:09:00.641 position:33% line:83% align:start
on attacking
my arms or legs anymore,

00:09:00.674 --> 00:09:02.743 position:13% line:89% align:start
like he knows it's useless.

00:09:02.777 --> 00:09:04.078 position:16% line:83% align:start
So he's only pinpointing
my vital areas

00:09:04.111 --> 00:09:06.447 position:19% line:89% align:start
like my face and chest,

00:09:06.480 --> 00:09:08.215 position:16% line:83% align:start
knowing that if his fist
touched me there,

00:09:08.249 --> 00:09:09.083 position:30% line:89% align:start
it'll be fatal!

00:09:10.251 --> 00:09:12.153 position:19% line:89% align:start
Plus, he dodged my kick

00:09:12.186 --> 00:09:14.755 position:19% line:83% align:start
and managed to get out
of the way by just millimeters!

00:09:15.890 --> 00:09:18.259 position:35% line:83% align:start
Which means,
this is a remote control Stan!

00:09:19.493 --> 00:09:21.595 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:09:21.629 --> 00:09:23.230 position:21% line:83% align:start
The priest has to be
around here

00:09:23.264 --> 00:09:24.999 position:13% line:89% align:start
watching with his own eyes.

00:09:25.032 --> 00:09:27.835 position:13% line:83% align:start
In other words, his Stand's
movements are so accurate

00:09:27.868 --> 00:09:29.303 position:21% line:83% align:start
because he's watching
every attack!

00:09:29.336 --> 00:09:31.038 position:27% line:83% align:start
This guy's Stand
causes destruction

00:09:31.072 --> 00:09:33.508 position:16% line:89% align:start
by manipulating gravity,

00:09:33.542 --> 00:09:36.010 position:27% line:83% align:start
so it just seems
like he's powerful.

