[Jolyne groans in pain]

00:17:18.272 --> 00:17:20.374 position:24% line:89% align:start
[melancholic music]

00:17:23.678 --> 00:17:26.246 position:13% line:89% align:start
All right, let's head back.

00:17:26.280 --> 00:17:28.448 position:19% line:83% align:start
We'll continue waiting
in the Visitor Center.

00:17:29.918 --> 00:17:31.084 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne breathing heavily]

00:17:31.586 --> 00:17:33.588 position:30% line:89% align:start
[pained scream]

00:17:33.621 --> 00:17:35.255 position:35% line:89% align:start
[both gasp]

00:17:35.289 --> 00:17:37.224 position:21% line:89% align:start
[screaming continues]

00:17:38.726 --> 00:17:39.627 position:38% line:89% align:start
[retches]

00:17:40.093 --> 00:17:42.329 position:30% line:89% align:start
What the hell?

00:17:42.362 --> 00:17:44.197 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Father Pucchi]
This battle is over.

00:17:44.231 --> 00:17:46.233 position:21% line:83% align:start
Jolyne can no longer
feel any pain

00:17:46.266 --> 00:17:49.403 position:24% line:83% align:start
or have the ability
to use cognitive functions.

00:17:49.436 --> 00:17:51.839 position:16% line:83% align:start
Her heart has been turned
inside out.

00:17:51.873 --> 00:17:53.106 position:30% line:83% align:start
The blood meant
for her brain

00:17:53.140 --> 00:17:54.107 position:19% line:83% align:start
should also be flowing
in reverse.

00:17:54.809 --> 00:17:57.679 position:13% line:89% align:start
Keep on pulling, Anastasia!

00:17:57.712 --> 00:18:01.015 position:10% line:83% align:start
Hey, hurry up! Pull Jolyne's
body back down here!

00:18:01.049 --> 00:18:03.116 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Anastasia grumbles]

00:18:03.150 --> 00:18:06.219 position:16% line:83% align:start
[groans] Jolyne's threads
are pulling apart!

00:18:07.187 --> 00:18:08.255 position:33% line:89% align:start
[body cracks]

00:18:10.324 --> 00:18:12.192 position:38% line:89% align:start
[groans]

00:18:12.225 --> 00:18:13.895 position:30% line:89% align:start
[tragic music]

00:18:13.928 --> 00:18:14.662 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Anastasia whimpers]

00:18:16.898 --> 00:18:17.665 position:38% line:89% align:start
No way...

00:18:19.634 --> 00:18:21.134 position:27% line:89% align:start
No, it can't be!

00:18:23.403 --> 00:18:26.139 position:41% line:89% align:start
[wails]

00:18:27.075 --> 00:18:29.711 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Anastasia] Jolyne!

00:18:33.681 --> 00:18:36.084 position:21% line:89% align:start
It will need a name.

00:18:36.116 --> 00:18:38.352 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'll call this new ability
See Moon.

00:18:39.654 --> 00:18:40.822 position:30% line:89% align:start
Invincibility.

00:18:43.290 --> 00:18:45.125 position:7% line:89% align:start
Is that the power I've obtained

00:18:45.158 --> 00:18:47.127 position:19% line:83% align:start
even before the coming
of the new moon?

00:18:49.296 --> 00:18:51.498 position:19% line:83% align:start
However, I must keep on
telling myself

00:18:51.532 --> 00:18:53.601 position:7% line:89% align:start
it is not power which I desire,

00:18:53.635 --> 00:18:56.269 position:10% line:83% align:start
but rather, what I truly long
for is the ultimate happiness

00:18:56.303 --> 00:19:00.273 position:19% line:83% align:start
that every human being
has the potential to achieve.

00:19:00.307 --> 00:19:01.308 position:13% line:89% align:start
And Jolyne Cujoh was merely

00:19:01.341 --> 00:19:02.877 position:13% line:83% align:start
a sacrificial pawn towards
that end.

00:19:04.211 --> 00:19:06.748 position:16% line:83% align:start
The same goes for Weather
and the other prisoners

00:19:06.781 --> 00:19:09.050 position:7% line:89% align:start
who valiantly gave their lives

00:19:09.083 --> 00:19:11.385 position:35% line:83% align:start
to further
my righteous objective.

00:19:11.418 --> 00:19:14.187 position:7% line:89% align:start
Their sacrifice was necessary.

00:19:14.221 --> 00:19:16.256 position:41% line:83% align:start
[sobs]
No, there's just no way.

00:19:16.289 --> 00:19:19.994 position:21% line:83% align:start
W-What do we do now?
J-Jolyne!

00:19:20.028 --> 00:19:21.194 position:41% line:83% align:start
[sobs]
I can't believe that...

00:19:21.562 --> 00:19:23.463 position:41% line:89% align:start
[wails]

00:19:24.065 --> 00:19:26.266 position:19% line:89% align:start
It just isn't possible!

00:19:26.299 --> 00:19:28.168 position:30% line:89% align:start
[tragic music]

00:19:36.978 --> 00:19:37.879 position:38% line:89% align:start
[sobbing]

00:19:38.780 --> 00:19:39.914 position:16% line:89% align:start
[phone rings in distance]

00:19:40.414 --> 00:19:41.314 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:19:42.016 --> 00:19:42.750 position:41% line:89% align:start
What...

00:19:43.818 --> 00:19:45.252 position:24% line:89% align:start
What's that sound?

00:19:45.753 --> 00:19:47.287 position:33% line:89% align:start
[phone rings]

00:19:47.320 --> 00:19:49.657 position:24% line:89% align:start
My phone! But how?

00:19:50.357 --> 00:19:51.726 position:16% line:89% align:start
It wasn't working before.

00:19:53.226 --> 00:19:54.595 position:21% line:89% align:start
I got a text message.

00:19:55.163 --> 00:19:57.665 position:21% line:89% align:start
But, who is it from?

00:19:57.699 --> 00:19:58.331 position:41% line:89% align:start
[beeps]

00:19:59.767 --> 00:20:02.070 position:33% line:83% align:start
[male voice]
My calls aren't going through.

00:20:02.103 --> 00:20:03.137 position:7% line:89% align:start
The gravitational anomaly seems

00:20:03.171 --> 00:20:05.673 position:33% line:83% align:start
to have sent
a satellite out of orbit.

00:20:07.075 --> 00:20:08.341 position:27% line:89% align:start
Are you Emporio?

00:20:09.276 --> 00:20:10.277 position:21% line:83% align:start
I don't know exactly
what's going on,

00:20:11.779 --> 00:20:12.680 position:21% line:89% align:start
but I can sense that

00:20:12.714 --> 00:20:14.347 position:35% line:83% align:start
my daughter
and the priest have met.

00:20:15.282 --> 00:20:16.951 position:44% line:83% align:start
Wait.
Could this text be from...

00:20:18.753 --> 00:20:19.921 position:30% line:89% align:start
Could it be...

00:20:20.822 --> 00:20:22.255 position:13% line:89% align:start
The person who sent this...

00:20:23.457 --> 00:20:25.159 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Jotaro] Jolyne is alive.

00:20:25.193 --> 00:20:26.994 position:24% line:89% align:start
But she's not safe.

00:20:27.929 --> 00:20:29.163 position:30% line:89% align:start
Protect Jolyne.

00:20:29.197 --> 00:20:33.835 position:19% line:83% align:start
Just until I arrive...
that's all I ask.

00:20:33.868 --> 00:20:36.604 position:16% line:83% align:start
She must have discovered
how to counter his gravity.

00:20:36.637 --> 00:20:39.006 position:24% line:83% align:start
That's the only way
she could have survived.

00:20:39.040 --> 00:20:41.241 position:10% line:89% align:start
She's alive, but just barely.

00:20:42.643 --> 00:20:44.311 position:33% line:89% align:start
Jotaro Kujo.

00:20:44.344 --> 00:20:45.847 position:19% line:89% align:start
Yeah, it is Mr. Jotaro.

00:20:45.880 --> 00:20:47.280 position:21% line:89% align:start
He must be close by.

00:20:48.816 --> 00:20:51.251 position:16% line:89% align:start
I... I can't believe it.

00:20:51.284 --> 00:20:53.821 position:7% line:83% align:start
Jolyne's actually still alive!
[gasps]

00:20:54.889 --> 00:20:55.288 position:24% line:89% align:start
Then that means...

00:20:56.991 --> 00:20:58.458 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Emporio sobs]
Could it be...?

00:20:59.292 --> 00:21:02.130 position:35% line:83% align:start
Anastasia,
you gotta find Jolyne!

00:21:02.163 --> 00:21:03.831 position:24% line:83% align:start
I think that Jolyne
is still alive!

00:21:04.999 --> 00:21:06.333 position:38% line:89% align:start
For real?

00:21:06.366 --> 00:21:09.837 position:16% line:83% align:start
Yeah, but that also means
that... that Pucchi knows.

00:21:09.871 --> 00:21:11.139 position:10% line:83% align:start
Since he has the same ability
to sense her,

00:21:11.172 --> 00:21:14.742 position:30% line:83% align:start
he's aware that
she's still alive too!

00:21:14.776 --> 00:21:17.344 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Father Pucchi]
What's going on, Jolyne Cujoh?

00:21:17.377 --> 00:21:19.614 position:16% line:83% align:start
Her heart should've been
turned inside out!

00:21:20.848 --> 00:21:22.083 position:19% line:89% align:start
My gravitational power

00:21:22.116 --> 00:21:23.718 position:19% line:83% align:start
should've destroyed it
completely!

00:21:24.218 --> 00:21:25.219 position:33% line:89% align:start
[tense music]

00:21:25.253 --> 00:21:27.221 position:27% line:83% align:start
How in the world
is she still alive?

00:21:27.255 --> 00:21:28.656 position:27% line:89% align:start
What did she do?

00:21:28.689 --> 00:21:30.490 position:10% line:89% align:start
I have to put an end to this.

00:21:30.525 --> 00:21:32.960 position:21% line:83% align:start
The Joestar bloodline
is something I must overcome,

00:21:32.994 --> 00:21:34.427 position:16% line:89% align:start
no matter what it takes!

00:21:34.996 --> 00:21:36.731 position:33% line:89% align:start
Diver Drive!

00:21:37.265 --> 00:21:38.331 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gurgling]

00:21:41.169 --> 00:21:44.038 position:33% line:89% align:start
[whimpering]

00:21:44.071 --> 00:21:46.373 position:41% line:83% align:start
[gasps]
Which way are you going?

00:21:46.841 --> 00:21:49.309 position:33% line:89% align:start
Take a guess.

00:21:49.342 --> 00:21:51.411 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Anastasia]
In order to protect Jolyne,

00:21:51.444 --> 00:21:54.081 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'm gonna have to kill
that fucking priest!

00:21:54.115 --> 00:21:55.082 position:27% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music]

00:22:10.665 --> 00:22:13.034 position:24% line:83% align:start
["Distant Dreamer"
by Duffy playing]

